    <h2 class="SubTitleFont">Matthew Reimherr - Assistant Professor</h2>
    <p class="BodyFont">I am an Assistant Professor in the Department of Statistics at Penn State University. Prior to coming here I was a PhD student at the University of Chicago.</p>
    <h2 class="SubTitleFont">Research Interests</h2>
    <p class="BodyFont">My work is primarily concerned with the theoretical development and application of methods for functional data.   Applied FDA areas I am particularly interested in are the high frequency settings encountered in financial econometrics, and the sparse longitudinal settings encountered in genetic association studies. <br />
    </p>
    <p><span class="BodyFont">Some of my other research interests include time series analysis, change point analysis, statistical genetics, quantifying prior impact on Bayesian analyses, and the intersection of de</span><span class="BodyFont">pendence and information theory. </span>
      <!-- end .content -->    </p>
